he Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Sutton was born before 1155, in Holderness, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom as the son of Sayer Sutton and Edith Grosse. He had at least 2 sons with Mabell Bardolfe. He died before 1186."},"et":{"Bef 1155–before 1186":"enne 1155–enne 1186","1155–1186":"1155–1186","1175–Male":"1175–Surnud","1176–Male":"1176–Surnud","1177–Male":"1177–Surnud","1215–1237":"1215–1237","1220–Male":"1220–Surnud","–1173":"–1173","–Female":"Surnud","1140–Female":"1140–Surnud","1166–1208":"1166–1208","1173–1264":"1173–1264","1135–1186":"1135–1186","before 1166":"enne 1166","1264":"1264","1220":"1220","1176":"1176","1175":"1175","1186":"1186","1173":"1173","1140":"1140","Bef 1186":"enne 1186","1237":"1237","1215":"1215","1135":"1135","Bef 1155":"enne 1155","1166":"1166","1177":"1177","1155":"1155","before 1186":"enne 1186","1208":"1208","Holderness, Yorkshire, England":"Holderness, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"Bef 1155–before 1186":"ennen vuotta 1155–ennen vuotta 1186","1155–1186":"1155–1186","1175–Male":"1175–Kuollut","1176–Male":"1176–Kuollut","1177–Male":"1177–Kuollut","1215–1237":"1215–1237","1220–Male":"1220–Kuollut","–1173":"–1173","–Female":"Kuollut","1140–Female":"1140–Kuollut","1166–1208":"1166–1208","1173–1264":"1173–1264","1135–1186":"1135–1186","before 1166":"ennen vuotta 1166","1264":"1264","1220":"1220","1176":"1176","1175":"1175","1186":"1186","1173":"1173","1140":"1140","Bef 1186":"ennen vuotta 1186","1237":"1237","1215":"1215","1135":"1135","Bef 1155":"ennen vuotta 1155","1166":"1166","1177":"1177","1155":"1155","before 1186":"ennen vuotta 1186","1208":"1208","Holderness, 